events.description: Hatshepsut dies at the age of 50 and is buried in the Valley of the Kings.
events.html: • 1458 BC – Hatshepsut dies at the age of 50 and is buried in the Valley of the Kings.[1]

events.description: Gaius Julius Caesar Octavianus is granted the title Augustus by the Roman Senate, marking the beginning of the Roman Empire.
events.html: • 27 BC – Gaius Julius Caesar Octavianus is granted the title Augustus by the Roman Senate, marking the beginning of the Roman Empire.[2]

events.description: General Siyaj K'ak' conquers Tikal, enlarging the domain of King Spearthrower Owl of Teotihuacán.
events.html: • 378 – General Siyaj K'ak' conquers Tikal, enlarging the domain of King Spearthrower Owl of Teotihuacán.[3]

events.description: Gothic War: The Ostrogoths, under King Totila, conquer Rome after a long siege, by bribing the Isaurian garrison.
events.html: • 550 – Gothic War: The Ostrogoths, under King Totila, conquer Rome after a long siege, by bribing the Isaurian garrison.[4]

events.description: Emir Abd-ar-Rahman III establishes the Caliphate of Córdoba.
events.html: • 929 – Emir Abd-ar-Rahman III establishes the Caliphate of Córdoba.[5]

events.description: Crusades: The Council of Nablus is held, establishing the earliest surviving written laws of the Crusader Kingdom of Jerusalem.
events.html: • 1120 – Crusades: The Council of Nablus is held, establishing the earliest surviving written laws of the Crusader Kingdom of Jerusalem.[6]

events.description: Saint Marcellus's flood kills at least 25,000 people on the shores of the North Sea.
events.html: • 1362 – Saint Marcellus's flood kills at least 25,000 people on the shores of the North Sea.[7]

events.description: Bigod's Rebellion, an armed insurrection attempting to resist the English Reformation, begins.
events.html: • 1537 – Bigod's Rebellion, an armed insurrection attempting to resist the English Reformation, begins.[8]

events.description: Grand Duke Ivan IV of Muscovy becomes the first Tsar of Russia, replacing the 264-year-old Grand Duchy of Moscow with the Tsardom of Russia.
events.html: • 1547 – Grand Duke Ivan IV of Muscovy becomes the first Tsar of Russia, replacing the 264-year-old Grand Duchy of Moscow with the Tsardom of Russia.[9]

events.description: Philip II becomes King of Spain.
events.html: • 1556 – Philip II becomes King of Spain.[10]

events.description: Thomas Howard, 4th Duke of Norfolk is tried and found guilty of treason for his part in the Ridolfi plot to restore Catholicism in England.
events.html: • 1572 – Thomas Howard, 4th Duke of Norfolk is tried and found guilty of treason for his part in the Ridolfi plot to restore Catholicism in England.[11]

events.description: The first edition of El ingenioso hidalgo Don Quijote de la Mancha (Book One of Don Quixote) by Miguel de Cervantes is published in Madrid, Spain.
events.html: • 1605 – The first edition of El ingenioso hidalgo Don Quijote de la Mancha (Book One of Don Quixote) by Miguel de Cervantes is published in Madrid, Spain.

events.description: The Scottish Parliament ratifies the Act of Union, paving the way for the creation of Great Britain.
events.html: • 1707 – The Scottish Parliament ratifies the Act of Union, paving the way for the creation of Great Britain.[12]

events.description: King Philip V of Spain promulgates the Nueva Planta decree of the Principality of Catalonia, abolishing the Catalan institutions and most of its legislation, being replaced by those of the Castile, thus putting an end to Catalonia as a separate political entity and becoming a province of the new French-style Kingdom of Spain.
events.html: • 1716 – King Philip V of Spain promulgates the Nueva Planta decree of the Principality of Catalonia, abolishing the Catalan institutions and most of its legislation, being replaced by those of the Castile, thus putting an end to Catalonia as a separate political entity and becoming a province of the new French-style Kingdom of Spain.[13]

events.description: Forces of the Maratha Empire defeat a 5,000-strong army of the Durrani Empire in the Battle of Narela.
events.html: • 1757 – Forces of the Maratha Empire defeat a 5,000-strong army of the Durrani Empire in the Battle of Narela.[14]

events.description: American Revolutionary War: Battle of Cape St. Vincent.
events.html: • 1780 – American Revolutionary War: Battle of Cape St. Vincent.[15]

events.description: Virginia enacts the Statute for Religious Freedom authored by Thomas Jefferson.
events.html: • 1786 – Virginia enacts the Statute for Religious Freedom authored by Thomas Jefferson.[16]

events.description: Peninsular War: The British defeat the French at the Battle of La Coruña.
events.html: • 1809 – Peninsular War: The British defeat the French at the Battle of La Coruña.

events.description: Westward expansion of the United States: John C. Frémont is appointed Governor of the new California Territory.
events.html: • 1847 – Westward expansion of the United States: John C. Frémont is appointed Governor of the new California Territory.

entities.name: Westward expansion of the United States

events.description: Hartley Colliery disaster: Two hundred and four men and boys killed in a mining disaster, prompting a change in UK law which henceforth required all collieries to have at least two independent means of escape.
events.html: • 1862 – Hartley Colliery disaster: Two hundred and four men and boys killed in a mining disaster, prompting a change in UK law which henceforth required all collieries to have at least two independent means of escape.[17]

events.description: Russo-Turkish War (1877–78): Battle of Philippopolis: Captain Aleksandr Burago with a squadron of Russian Imperial army dragoons liberates Plovdiv from Ottoman rule.
events.html: • 1878 – Russo-Turkish War (1877–78): Battle of Philippopolis: Captain Aleksandr Burago with a squadron of Russian Imperial army dragoons liberates Plovdiv from Ottoman rule.

events.description: The Pendleton Civil Service Reform Act, establishing the United States Civil Service, is enacted by Congress.
events.html: • 1883 – The Pendleton Civil Service Reform Act, establishing the United States Civil Service, is enacted by Congress.[18]

events.description: The United States Senate accepts the Anglo-German treaty of 1899 in which the United Kingdom renounces its claims to the Samoan islands.
events.html: • 1900 – The United States Senate accepts the Anglo-German treaty of 1899 in which the United Kingdom renounces its claims to the Samoan islands.

events.description: Ernest Shackleton's expedition finds the magnetic South Pole.
events.html: • 1909 – Ernest Shackleton's expedition finds the magnetic South Pole.[19]

events.description: Nebraska becomes the 36th state to approve the Eighteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution. With the necessary three-quarters of the states approving the amendment, Prohibition is constitutionally mandated in the United States one year later.
events.html: • 1919 – Nebraska becomes the 36th state to approve the Eighteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution. With the necessary three-quarters of the states approving the amendment, Prohibition is constitutionally mandated in the United States one year later.[20]

entities.name: Eighteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution

events.description: The League of Nations holds its first council meeting in Paris, France.
events.html: • 1920 – The League of Nations holds its first council meeting in Paris, France.

events.description: The Marxist Left in Slovakia and the Transcarpathian Ukraine holds its founding congress in Ľubochňa.
events.html: • 1921 – The Marxist Left in Slovakia and the Transcarpathian Ukraine holds its founding congress in Ľubochňa.

entities.name: Marxist Left in Slovakia and the Transcarpathian Ukraine

events.description: The Holocaust: Nazi Germany begins deporting Jews from the Łódź Ghetto to Chełmno extermination camp.
events.html: • 1942 – The Holocaust: Nazi Germany begins deporting Jews from the Łódź Ghetto to Chełmno extermination camp.[21]

events.description: Crash of TWA Flight 3, killing all 22 aboard, including film star Carole Lombard.
events.html: • 1942 – Crash of TWA Flight 3, killing all 22 aboard, including film star Carole Lombard.[22]

events.description: World War II: Adolf Hitler moves into his underground bunker, the so-called Führerbunker.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: Adolf Hitler moves into his underground bunker, the so-called Führerbunker.

events.description: Austral Líneas Aéreas Flight 205 crashes into the Atlantic Ocean near Astor Piazzolla International Airport in Mar del Plata, Argentina, killing 51.
events.html: • 1959 – Austral Líneas Aéreas Flight 205 crashes into the Atlantic Ocean near Astor Piazzolla International Airport in Mar del Plata, Argentina, killing 51.[23]

events.description: Czech student Jan Palach commits suicide by self-immolation in Prague, Czechoslovakia, in protest against the Soviets' crushing of the Prague Spring the year before.
events.html: • 1969 – Czech student Jan Palach commits suicide by self-immolation in Prague, Czechoslovakia, in protest against the Soviets' crushing of the Prague Spring the year before.[24]

events.description: Space Race: Soviet spacecraft Soyuz 4 and Soyuz 5 perform the first-ever docking of crewed spacecraft in orbit, the first-ever transfer of crew from one space vehicle to another, and the only time such a transfer was accomplished with a space walk.
events.html: • 1969 – Space Race: Soviet spacecraft Soyuz 4 and Soyuz 5 perform the first-ever docking of crewed spacecraft in orbit, the first-ever transfer of crew from one space vehicle to another, and the only time such a transfer was accomplished with a space walk.

events.description: Iranian Revolution: The last Iranian Shah flees Iran with his family for good and relocates to Egypt.
events.html: • 1979 – Iranian Revolution: The last Iranian Shah flees Iran with his family for good and relocates to Egypt.[25]

events.description: Turkish Airlines Flight 158 crashes at Ankara Esenboğa Airport in Ankara, Turkey, killing 47 and injuring 20.
events.html: • 1983 – Turkish Airlines Flight 158 crashes at Ankara Esenboğa Airport in Ankara, Turkey, killing 47 and injuring 20.[26]

events.description: Coalition Forces go to war with Iraq, beginning the Gulf War.
events.html: • 1991 – Coalition Forces go to war with Iraq, beginning the Gulf War.

events.description: El Salvador officials and rebel leaders sign the Chapultepec Peace Accords in Mexico City, Mexico ending the 12-year Salvadoran Civil War that claimed at least 75,000 lives.
events.html: • 1992 – El Salvador officials and rebel leaders sign the Chapultepec Peace Accords in Mexico City, Mexico ending the 12-year Salvadoran Civil War that claimed at least 75,000 lives.

events.description: An avalanche hits the Icelandic village Súðavík, destroying 25 homes and burying 26 people, 14 of whom died.
events.html: • 1995 – An avalanche hits the Icelandic village Súðavík, destroying 25 homes and burying 26 people, 14 of whom died.[27]

events.description: Second Congo War: Congolese President Laurent-Désiré Kabila is assassinated by one of his own bodyguards in Kinshasa.
events.html: • 2001 – Second Congo War: Congolese President Laurent-Désiré Kabila is assassinated by one of his own bodyguards in Kinshasa.[28]

events.description: US President Bill Clinton awards former President Theodore Roosevelt a posthumous Medal of Honor for his service in the Spanish–American War.
events.html: • 2001 – US President Bill Clinton awards former President Theodore Roosevelt a posthumous Medal of Honor for his service in the Spanish–American War.

events.description: War in Afghanistan: The UN Security Council unanimously establishes an arms embargo and the freezing of assets of Osama bin Laden, al-Qaeda, and the remaining members of the Taliban.
events.html: • 2002 – War in Afghanistan: The UN Security Council unanimously establishes an arms embargo and the freezing of assets of Osama bin Laden, al-Qaeda, and the remaining members of the Taliban.

events.description: The Space Shuttle Columbia takes off for mission STS-107 which would be its final one. Columbia disintegrated 16 days later on re-entry.
events.html: • 2003 – The Space Shuttle Columbia takes off for mission STS-107 which would be its final one. Columbia disintegrated 16 days later on re-entry.

events.description: Ellen Johnson Sirleaf is sworn in as Liberia's new president. She becomes Africa's first female elected head of state.
events.html: • 2006 – Ellen Johnson Sirleaf is sworn in as Liberia's new president. She becomes Africa's first female elected head of state.[29]

events.description: Syrian civil war: The Movement for a Democratic Society (TEV-DEM) is established with the stated goal of re-organizing Syria along the lines of democratic confederalism.
events.html: • 2011 – Syrian civil war: The Movement for a Democratic Society (TEV-DEM) is established with the stated goal of re-organizing Syria along the lines of democratic confederalism.[30][31]

events.html: • 2016 – Thirty-three out of 126 freed hostages are injured and 23 killed in terrorist attacks in Ouagadougou, Burkina Faso on a hotel and a nearby restaurant.
